ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I need to get a handle on my anxiety and fear for me to have the life I want.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: Appearing nervous is not good and causes me to suffer.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: I can't really do the things that I want to do when I have anxiety and fear.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: I must stay in control of my emotions.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: If I were like other people, I would be able to get a grip on my anxious thoughts and feelings.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: My anxious thoughts and feelings are a problem.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: I am sure to be embarrassed and make a fool of myself when other people notice how nervous and shaky I feel.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: Unusual body sensations are scary and something I need to act on to reduce or get rid of before I can do anything else.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: My anxious thoughts and feelings are not normal.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: Scanning my body for signs and symptoms of anxiety is important to keep me safe.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: When I am very anxious or afraid, there is a good chance that I might be dying.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: I could lose control of myself when I feel anxious or afraid.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: I must do something about my anxiety or fear when it shows up.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: When unpleasant thoughts occur, I must push them out of my mind.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: When I feel bad, I must fight the feeling in order to make it go away.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable

ElementDescription: My happiness and success depend on how good I feel.
Notes: 1 = Not at all believable; 7 = Completely believable
